Program: Omnibus
Title: Uganda
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376jd9
Last Broadcast Date: 10 December 1986
How life in Uganda is progressing after the brutal regime of Idi Amin and the Ugandan Bush War which followed. Church leaders talk about how Ugandans are dealing with the consequences of life under corruption and brutality. Picture: Flag of Uganda, Credit: Getty Images